# 5. 私のエゴ

Kohane: My ego...
Kohane: (What fuels my ego...?)
Kohane: (What do I want to do no matter the cost, no matter how much trouble it causes...?)
Kohane: I really don't know.
Kohane: (There are plenty of things that I want to do.)
Kohane: (Win against Taiga and An just to list a couple of examples. And just the other day...)
Kohane: (I thought, “I want to see what it's like on the other side of that wall.”)
Kohane: (But I'm not sure if those things really count as having an ego.)
Kohane: (Nagi came up with a lie for An and went as far as getting all the locals to keep the truth a secret from her, all because that was what she wanted.)
Kohane: (Taiga went overseas by himself to try to make his team's dream come true...)
Kohane: (And An's dad decided to stay in Japan and open up a cafe to help the next generation grow.)
Kohane: (They all wanted to make those things happen no matter what, because of their egos.)
Kohane: (So, what is it that I want to do no matter the cost...?)
???: <Why the long face? Is something the matter?>
Kohane: Huh? Oh!
Kohane: Miku...!
Miku: <How are you? Also, how's your training going?>
Kohane: Oh, actually, I managed to complete my first task. Everyone said that I've made enough progress.
Miku: <Really? That's great, Kohane!>
Kohane: Thanks...
Miku: <But you don't seem all that happy despite such a big accomplishment.>
Miku: <Did something happen?>
Kohane: So, the thing is... I'm trying to master the way I sang while training to make sure that our event actually succeeds...
Kohane: I told the owner of COL about what I was feeling, and she said...
Miku: <Your ego...>
Kohane: Yeah, she said that I should try looking for what drives mine.
Kohane: But, I'm having a lot of trouble.
Kohane: I know that I want to see what it's like on the other side of that wall after we surpass RAD WEEKEND. But I'm not sure if that counts as having an ego...
Kohane: I'm starting to wonder if I even have something like that...
Miku: <What?>
Kohane: Ever since I was little, I never had any dreams or things that I really wanted to do...
Kohane: And I have a dream now only because I just happened to meet An...
Kohane: In other words, I needed someone else's help finding a dream for me to pursue...
Kohane: So, if you ask me if there's anything I want to do no matter the cost, no matter how much trouble it causes...
Miku: <There is.>
Kohane: Huh?
Miku: <There is something you want to do no matter what. You just haven't realized it yet, Kohane.>
Miku: <Just try to think.>
Miku: <At your very core, there's something that drives you do to what you do.>
Kohane: Something that drives me...?
Kohane: What is that...?
Miku: <Hey, Kohane.>
Miku: <Stressing yourself out like this isn't good for you, so why don't we go for a quick walk?>
Kohane: Huh?
Kohane: It feels like it's been so long since I just went for a stroll like this.
Miku: <You have been spending most of your time training lately.>
Miku: <So, how do you feel now after getting a chance to take a nice, relaxing walk?>
Kohane: How do I feel...? Umm...
Kohane: I am feeling pretty relaxed now...
Kohane: Hehe. Which is a little odd considering how scared I was when I first wandered into this part of the city...
Passerby A: Ahahahaha! What are you talking about?! You're so full of yourself!
Passerby B: Hey, what do you say we stay out all night?!
Kohane: I thought this place seemed a little dangerous at first because everyone around here was so different from me.
Miku: <Right. These were uncharted waters for the old you.>
Kohane: Hehe. They were. Finding myself in a place I'd never been before was so scary...
Kohane: But...
Kohane: That was also when I found Weekend Garage, and met An...
Kohane: After I'd worked up the courage to open the door, An and these other musicians all began singing...
Kohane: Seeing that really made my heart race.
Miku: <I see.>
Kohane: Huh?
Kohane: I hear people singing...
Miku: <Me too... Could it be...?>
Miku: <Why don't we go see...?>
Kohane: Okay!
Kohane: (Yeah, it's coming from inside...)
Kohane: (It's just like that time.)
Kohane: (I went up to the door, opened it and...)
Akito: ♪ーーーー!!
Toya: ♪————!! ————!!
An: ♪———————————~~~!!
Kohane: (They sound amazing...)
Kohane: (I'm getting goosebumps... My heart's beating so fast...)
Kohane: (“More”...)
Kohane: (I don't know if this has anything to do with my ego...)
Kohane: (But I really love this feeling.)
Kohane: (If I'm going to sing at the event that surpasses RAD WEEKEND, then I want to do it with this feeling.)
Kohane: (I want to feel even more excited.)
Kohane: (I want to make everyone else feel more excited.)
Kohane: (I want to sing with that feeling at my core.)
Ken: Alright, you all seem to be coming along nicely, so let's call things here for today.
Toya, An & Akito: *Nod* Okay!
Kotaro: That last song was insane! You guys sent shivers down my spine!
Tatsuya: That means we've still got some work left to do. I mean, we can't let you guys hog all the glory!
An: Hehe. Then, do your best, you guys!
An: Huh? Kohane?!
An: You startled us! Didn't you say you were gonna head straight home from COL?
Toya: Yes, it's getting very late... Shouldn't you be resting at home instead?
Kohane: Yeah, that was my plan...
Kohane: I couldn't help but open the door after hearing all of you singing...
Kohane: So, umm... If it's alright with you guys...
Kohane: How about one more song?
An: Huh?
Kohane: I really want to sing now after hearing all of you!
Ken: (I was a little worried since she seemed pretty unsure when I left her at COL...)
Ken: (But she seems fine now.)
An: Okay! Then, let's do one more!
Toya: Yes, since Azusawa's here.
Akito: Alright, this'll be our last song for today. Let's give it everything we've got.
Kohane: Thanks, you guys!
Miku: <I'm sure you'll do just fine.>
Miku: <Because you've never once run away from your feelings.>
Kohane: Miku...
Kohane: Thanks, I really appreciate it...!
Kohane: (She's right... I was put to the test over and over along the way, but I'm standing here right now because I kept trying.)
Kohane: (I mean, I've overcome so much...!)
Miku: <Just one week to go. Do your best.>
Kohane: I will!
Kohane & An: ♪————————!
Akito: Alright, now we're on the same page, let's do one more!
Toya: Okay!
Everyone: ♪————————————————————!
An: Phew... Ending practice this early feels kinda weird.
Kohane: Hehe. I know what you mean. It's been a while since we've been practicing so late each day.
Kohane: ... Tomorrow's the big day.
Akito: Yeah.
Kotaro: *Sigh* I hope I can get some sleep tonight.
Tatsuya: I was going to poke fun at you for that, but I totally feel the same way.
Toya: This is the wall of all walls for us.
Akito: Yeah... But I'm excited since it's finally happening.
Kotaro: Excited? Not nervous or anxious...?
EVER Member A: Haha. But we feel ready now thanks to you guys.
Tatsuya: Still, it's sad that we're down one person...
Kohane: Oh...
Kohane: ...
Kotaro: We gotta make this event so good that he's gonna really regret not coming back to do it with us!
Kotaro: Then, he might become so frustrated that he won't have any other choice but to come back.
Tatsuya: Yeah, maybe.
Toya: ...
Akito: You look like you still haven't given up.
Toya: ...! Akito...
Toya: No, I haven't... I still want us to take on this challenge together.
Akito: Yeah, I'm with you there.
Akito: But he has to make his own decisions. There's nothing we can do about that.
Toya: True...
Akito: So, we'll be carrying his dream with us...
Akito: His dream of those two surpassing that night together.
Toya: Right.
Akito: Regardless, we've done everything we possibly can. There's no two ways about that.
Akito: All that's left is for us to do it.
Kohane: ... Right.
Tatsuya: How about you, Azusawa? I know you have nerves of steel, but are you feeling anxious at all?
Kohane: I...
Kohane: I'm honestly a little scared.
Kohane: Because we find out tomorrow whether or not we're able to surpass RAD WEEKEND... It's a terrifying prospect...
An: Kohane...
Kohane: But... The thing is...
Kohane: I also can't wait for tomorrow.
Kohane: I can't wait to put on the best event ever with all of you.
An: ... Yeah.
An: Let's do it! Let's put on the best event this neighborhood's ever seen! It's gonna be the greatest night ever! Completely new and unprecedented!
An: And after we do, we're not gonna know what to do with ourselves!
Tatsuya: Yeah, it's probably gonna feel a hundred times better than cruising down the coast on my motorcycle.
Kotaro: Totally! Or it'll be like eating all the good food you'll ever have all at once... No, better than that!
Toya: I'm excited just thinking about tomorrow.
Akito: It's happening tomorrow, guys.
Akito: We're gonna surpass RAD WEEKEND!!
Everyone: Yeah! Yes! Okay!
